            <h3><b>Which Financial Goals Can Life Insurance Help You Achieve?</b></h3>
           
            
            <p>Understanding the purpose of life insurance and the concept of life insurance may not be enough to meet your specific needs. Life insurance plans can help a person and his family achieve a variety of financial goals. Some of the aims that the finest life insurance policy can assist an individual achieve include:</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li>Financial Security against death.</li>
                <li>Monthly income or Post Retirement Pension</li>
                <li>Marriage of Children.</li>
                <li>Child’s Education</li>
                <li>Owning/Purchasing a Home</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p>These are just a few of the financial goals that life insurance plans can help you reach. Life insurance policies come with variety of features and benefits. You can plan for your stated life goals and align your insurance to assist you in achieving them, for example, you can utilise the corpus established by endowment plans (conventional or market-linked) to pay for a house at a later date.</p>
        </div>
        
        <br />
        <h3><b>Comparing Life Insurance Plans: </b></h3>
        
        <p>Because all life insurance companies offer different life insurance policies, it is critical to compare life insurance plans online. Furthermore, each life insurance business offers a variety of life insurance options. Analysing the best plan for oneself may appear to be a difficult undertaking. When comparing life insurance policies, consider the following factors:</p>
        
        <ul>
            <li>
                <b>Premium for Life Insurance:</b>
                <p>First and foremost, be sure you're getting enough life insurance and aren't over- or under-insured. After you've listed down a few policies based on their features and benefits, you'll need to compare the premiums for the same level of coverage supplied by each.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Life Insurance Plan Features:</b>
                <p>Compare the features of various life insurance plans offered by various life insurance firms. Always choose a comprehensive life insurance policy that allows you to customise the policy's duration, sum assured, premium payment mode and frequency, payouts, and other features to meet your specific needs.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Riders for Life Insurance:</b>
                <p>Riders are add-ons to your regular life insurance policy. The life insurance riders are add-ons that can be purchased for a fee. However, before purchasing a life insurance plan online, check to see if the riders you want are offered as an in-built option by another insurer. Some of the crucial riders you may want to include in your policy may be included as a component of a different life insurance company's plan. Make sure, though, that you only get riders if you truly need them, rather of just getting one and over-insuring your life insurance policy.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Claim Settlement Ratio:</b>
                <p>The Company’s claim settlement ratio represents the proportion of total claims settled versus total claims filed. Higher claim settlement ratio is better. A higher ratio indicates that your claim has a better likelihood of being settled. Every year, the claim settlement ratio for each life insurance company varies. As a result, while comparing life insurance products, it is an important issue to consider.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
